      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentSON\n2: \n3: **Agent + JSON** — The open interchange format for AI agent session traces.\n4: \n5: [![PyPI version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/agentson.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/agentson/)\n6: [![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-Apache%202.0-blue.svg)](LICENSE)\n7: [![Python](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/agentson.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/agentson/)\n8: [![CI](https://github.com/andiekobbietks/AgentSON/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/andiekobbietks/AgentSON/actions)\n9: \n10: > Nobody has done for agent session logs what OpenAPI did for REST APIs or what containers.dev did for dev environments.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Why This Exists\n15: \n16: This project started with a FreeStyle Libre 2 continuous glucose monitor.\n17: \n18: Managing a chronic condition means your most personal data — blood glucose readings every 5 minutes, 24/7 — lives inside a vendor's app. Abbott's FreeStyle Libre app stores your data. It doesn't export to JSON. It doesn't integrate with your AI tools. It doesn't connect to your doctor's system without jumping through NHS FHIR hoops.\n19: \n20: The same lock-in problem exists everywhere:\n21: \n22: | Domain | Vendor | Data trapped |\n23: |--------|--------|--------------|\n24: | Health | Abbott (FreeStyle Libre 2) | Glucose readings, trends, reports |\n25: | AI coding | OpenAI, Anthropic, Google | Session transcripts, reasoning traces |\n26: | Development | Cursor, Copilot, Claude Code | Code context, edit history |\n27: \n28: **GDPR Article 20** gives you the right to export your data in a machine-readable format. **The EU AI Act** requires transparency about AI-generated content. Most tools don't provide this. AgentSON does.\n29: \n30: The FreeStyle Libre reader (`readers/libre.py`) was the first reader built — not because glucose data is the most important, but because it's the most personal. If the format can handle medical time-series data, it can handle anything.\n31: \n32: > **Your health data. Your code sessions. Your data. One format.**\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## The Problem\n37: \n38: Every AI coding agent stores session data in its own proprietary database. There is no standard format, no export API, and no way to move context between tools. The data that powers AI training is locked inside vendor silos.\n39: \n40: ## The Solution\n41: \n42: AgentSON captures the full trajectory of what happened during an AI-assisted session: prompts, thoughts, actions, code, observations, and outcomes — in one portable JSON file.\n43: \n44: ```\n45: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n46: │                    AgentSON Architecture                     │\n47: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n48: │                                                             │\n49: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐        │\n50: │  │   Cursor    │  │ Claude Code │  │   opencode  │        │\n51: │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘        │\n52: │         │                │                │                  │\n53: │         ▼                ▼                ▼                  │\n54: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n55: │  │         .AgentSON Files (Open Spec)                  │   │\n56: │  │     Portable, vendor-neutral, file-based             │   │\n57: │  └─────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────┘   │\n58: │                             │                                │\n59: │              ┌──────────────┼──────────────┐               │\n60: │              ▼              ▼              ▼               │\n61: │  ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐      │\n62: │  │   Local CLI  │ │   Supabase   │ │  Web Viewer  │      │\n63: │  │  (offline)   │ │  (optional)  │ │   (shared)   │      │\n64: │  └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘      │\n65: │                                                             │\n66: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## Tool Landscape\n72: \n73: AgentSON covers the entire AI coding ecosystem — 33 tools across 7 tiers.\n74: \n75: ### Reader Coverage\n76: \n77: ```mermaid\n78: pie title Reader Coverage (v0.1.0)\n79:     \"Working (6)\" : 6\n80:     \"Planned (27)\" : 27\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ### RICE Priority (Top 10 Readers)\n84: \n85: ```mermaid\n86: xychart-beta\n87:     title \"RICE Score by Tool\"\n88:     x-axis [\"Cursor\", \"Copilot\", \"Claude\", \"Codex\", \"Gemini\", \"opencode\", \"Cline\", \"Aider\", \"Kiro\", \"Windsurf\"]\n89:     y-axis \"RICE Score\" 0 --> 5000\n90:     bar [2700, 4000, 2400, 1920, 1400, 9999, 1350, 1350, 1120, 480]\n91: ```\n92: \n93: > opencode (RICE: ∞) already works — zero effort, full reach.\n94: \n95: ### Tier 1: Core Market\n96: \n97: | # | Tool | Type | Pricing | Traces | AgentSON |\n98: |---|------|------|---------|--------|----------|\n99: | 1 | **Cursor** | IDE | $20-40/mo | Richest (70% Fortune 1000) | 🔜 Planned |\n100: | 2 | **Claude Code** | CLI | $20-200/mo | Deep reasoning (~$2.5B run-rate) | ✅ **Working** |\n101: | 3 | **Kiro** | IDE | Free-$200/mo | Spec-driven (structured by design) | 🔜 Planned |\n102: | 4 | **Codex CLI** | CLI | $20-200/mo | GPT-5.5 (ChatGPT base) | 🔜 Planned |\n103: | 5 | **Gemini CLI** | CLI | Free | 1M context (Apache 2.0) | 🔜 Planned |\n104: | 6 | **Windsurf/Devin Desktop** | IDE | $15-200/mo | ACP protocol (Cognition) | 🔜 Planned |\n105: \n106: ### Tier 2: Open Source\n107: \n108: | # | Tool | Type | Pricing | Traces | AgentSON |\n109: |---|------|------|---------|--------|----------|\n110: | 7 | **opencode** | CLI | Free (BYOK) | 147K stars, 6.5M devs | ✅ **Working** |\n111: | 8 | **Cline** | VS Code ext | Free (BYOK) | 60K stars, 5M installs | 🔜 Planned |\n112: | 9 | **Aider** | CLI | Free (BYOK) | 43K stars, MIT | 🔜 Planned |\n113: | 10 | **Zed** | IDE | Free + API | ACP protocol, parallel agents | 🔜 Planned |\n114: | 11 | **Goose** | CLI | Free (BYOK) | Apache 2.0, Block-backed | 🔜 Planned |\n115: | 12 | **OpenHands** | Web+CLI | Free (BYOK) | MIT, autonomous SWE | 🔜 Planned |\n116: \n117: ### Tier 3: Extensions\n118: \n119: | # | Tool | Type | Pricing | Traces | AgentSON |\n120: |---|------|------|---------|--------|----------|\n121: | 13 | **GitHub Copilot** | Multi-IDE | $10-39/mo | Widest reach (5M+ users) | 🔜 Planned |\n122: | 14 | **Amazon Q** | Extension | $19/user | AWS-native, enterprise | 🔜 Planned |\n123: | 15 | **JetBrains AI** | Built-in | $10/mo | 31% market share | 🔜 Planned |\n124: | 16 | **Sourcegraph Cody** | Extension | Free-$9/mo | Large codebase nav | 🔜 Planned |\n125: | 17 | **Qodo** | Extension | Free-$19/mo | Code review specialist | 🔜 Planned |\n126: | 18 | **Augment Code** | Extension | $20-60/mo | 200K context window | 🔜 Planned |\n127: | 19 | **Continue** | Extension | Free | Open-source, self-hosted | 🔜 Planned |\n128: | 20 | **Tabnine** | Extension | $12/mo | Privacy-focused, on-premise | 🔜 Planned |\n129: \n130: ### Tier 4: Builders\n131: \n132: | # | Tool | Type | Pricing | Traces | AgentSON |\n133: |---|------|------|---------|--------|----------|\n134: | 21 | **Bolt.new** | Browser | Free-$20/mo | Prompt→deploy | 🔜 Planned |\n135: | 22 | **v0** | Browser | Free-$20/mo | UI generation | 🔜 Planned |\n136: | 23 | **Lovable** | Browser | Free-$20/mo | Full-stack apps | 🔜 Planned |\n137: | 24 | **Replit** | Browser IDE | Free-$25/mo | Full environment | 🔜 Planned |\n138: \n139: ### Tier 5: Orchestrators\n140: \n141: | # | Tool | Type | Pricing | Traces | AgentSON |\n142: |---|------|------|---------|--------|----------|\n143: | 25 | **amux** | Web+PWA | Free (BYOK) | 20-50+ parallel agents | 🔜 Planned |\n144: | 26 | **Claude Squad** | TUI | Free (BYOK) | MIT, 10-20 agents | 🔜 Planned |\n145: | 27 | **Kilo Code** | IDE panel | Free-$199/mo | Apache 2.0 | 🔜 Planned |\n146: | 28 | **dmux** | Terminal | Free (BYOK) | MIT | 🔜 Planned |\n147: \n148: ### Tier 6: Autonomous\n149: \n150: | # | Tool | Type | Pricing | Traces | AgentSON |\n151: |---|------|------|---------|--------|----------|\n152: | 29 | **Devin** | Cloud SaaS | $20-500+/mo | Fully autonomous | 🔜 Planned |\n153: | 30 | **Blitzy** | Cloud SaaS | Enterprise | Enterprise SWE | 🔜 Planned |\n154: \n155: ### Tier 7: China Plans\n156: \n157: | # | Tool | Type | Pricing | Traces | AgentSON |\n158: |---|------|------|---------|--------|----------|\n159: | 31 | **GLM Coding** | Desktop+CLI | Subscription | GLM-5.2 | ⏸ Deferred |\n160: | 32 | **Kimi** | CLI | Cheap | Cost leader | ⏸ Deferred |\n161: | 33 | **Qwen Code** | CLI | Cheap | Growing in Asia | ⏸ Deferred |\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Why AgentSON Matters\n166: \n167: ### The Unsloth Analogy\n168: \n169: Unsloth democratized model fine-tuning. AgentSON democratizes data ownership.\n170: \n171: | Before | After |\n172: |--------|-------|\n173: | GPU cluster + PhD needed | Single GPU, hours |\n174: | No export API, vendor lock-in | One CLI command, portable JSON |\n175: | Big labs only | Everyone |\n176: \n177: ### But It's Locked In\n178: \n179: | Tool | Exports data? | Portable? | Trainable? |\n180: |------|--------------|-----------|------------|\n181: | Cursor | No | No | No |\n182: | Claude Code | No | No | No |\n183: | Copilot | Partial (API) | No | No |\n184: | **AgentSON** | **Yes (JSON)** | **Yes** | **Yes** |\n185: \n186: ### What AgentSON Gives You\n187: \n188: 1. **Portability** — Switch tools without losing context\n189: 2. **Training data** — Export to Unsloth/Olive for fine-tuning\n190: 3. **Search** — Full-text search across all your sessions\n191: 4. **Ownership** — No telemetry, no vendor lock-in, no cloud dependency\n192: 5. **Interoperability** — One format, all tools\n193: 6. **Legal compliance** — GDPR Art. 20 + EU AI Act Art. 52\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ## Quick Start\n198: \n199: ```bash\n200: # Install\n201: pip install agentson\n202: \n203: # List sessions\n204: agentson list --tool opencode\n205: \n206: # Export a session\n207: agentson export --tool opencode --session ses_xxx --output ./sessions/\n208: \n209: # Fine-tuning export (Unsloth format)\n210: agentson finetune *.AgentSON --format unsloth --output training.jsonl\n211: \n212: # Search across sessions\n213: agentson search \"nightscout\" --tool opencode\n214: \n215: # Render as Markdown\n216: agentson render session.AgentSON --format md\n217: \n218: # Push to Supabase (optional)\n219: agentson push session.AgentSON\n220: ```\n221: \n222: ---\n223: \n224: ## Schema (v1.1)\n225: \n226: ```json\n227: {\n228:   \"$schema\": \"https://agentson.dev/schema/v1.1.json\",\n229:   \"id\": \"session-2026-07-04-001\",\n230:   \"task\": \"Fix the authentication bug in the login flow\",\n231:   \"outcome\": \"success\",\n232:   \"tool\": {\"name\": \"opencode\", \"session_id\": \"ses_xxx\"},\n233:   \"agent\": {\"name\": \"mimo-v2.5-free\", \"provider\": \"opencode\"},\n234:   \"entries\": [\n235:     {\"type\": \"user-query\", \"text\": \"Fix the auth bug\"},\n236:     {\"type\": \"thought\", \"text\": \"Looking at the auth module...\"},\n237:     {\"type\": \"action\", \"tool\": \"bash\", \"code\": \"grep -r 'auth' src/\", \"tool_call_id\": \"tc_001\"},\n238:     {\"type\": \"observation\", \"text\": \"Found 3 files\", \"correlation_id\": \"tc_001\"},\n239:     {\"type\": \"answer\", \"text\": \"Fixed the null check in auth.py\"}\n240:   ]\n241: }\n242: ```\n243: \n244: ### Entry Types\n245: \n246: | Type | Description |\n247: |------|-------------|\n248: | `user-query` | User's input or question |\n249: | `context` | Additional context (data used, DOM info) |\n250: | `querying` | Agent is processing |\n251: | `title` | Section or step title |\n252: | `thought` | Agent's reasoning/thinking |\n253: | `action` | Tool execution (code + output) |\n254: | `answer` | Agent's response |\n255: | `side-effect` | File changes, state mutations |\n256: | `observation` | Async observation from tool/user/system |\n257: \n258: ---\n259: \n260: ## Fine-Tuning Export\n261: \n262: ```bash\n263: # Unsloth/ShareGPT format (for LLaMA, Mistral, etc.)\n264: agentson finetune *.AgentSON --format unsloth --output train.jsonl\n265: \n266: # Olive format (Microsoft Olive pipeline)\n267: agentson finetune *.AgentSON --format olive --output train.jsonl\n268: ```\n269: \n270: Example output:\n271: ```json\n272: {\n273:   \"conversations\": [\n274:     {\"from\": \"human\", \"value\": \"How do I fix the auth bug?\"},\n275:     {\"from\": \"gpt\", \"value\": \"I'll look at the auth module...\"}\n276:   ],\n277:   \"source\": \"opencode\",\n278:   \"session_id\": \"ses_xxx\"\n279: }\n280: ```\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## PWA Viewer\n285: \n286: Open `pwa/index.html` in a browser, drag-and-drop an `.AgentSON` file. Works offline.\n287: \n288: Full-featured web viewer at `docs/viewer/`: validation, download, search, sort, side-by-side layout, role-based colors.\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ## Repository Structure\n293: \n294: ```\n295: agentson/\n296: ├── spec/\n297: │   ├── v1.json              # JSON Schema v1\n298: │   └── v1.1.json            # JSON Schema v1.1 (trajectory semantics)\n299: ├── readers/                 # Tool-specific readers\n300: │   ├── opencode.py          # ✅ Working\n301: │   ├── minimax.py           # ✅ Working\n302: │   ├── antigravity.py       # ✅ Working\n303: │   ├── libre.py             # ✅ Working (FreeStyle Libre 2)\n304: │   ├── chrome_devtools.py   # ✅ Working (9 tests)\n305: │   └── claude_code.py       # ✅ Working\n306: ├── importers/\n307: │   └── chatgpt.py           # ✅ ChatGPT conversations.json\n308: ├── exporters/\n309: │   └── finetune.py          # ✅ Unsloth + Olive formats\n310: ├── cli/\n311: │   ├── main.py              # CLI entry point\n312: │   └── supabase_client.py   # Supabase integration\n313: ├── tests/\n314: │   └── test_chrome_devtools.py  # ✅ 9 tests\n315: ├── examples/                # Example .AgentSON files\n316: ├── pwa/                     # PWA viewer\n317: ├── docs/                    # Live docs + viewer\n318: │   ├── viewer/              # Web viewer\n319: │   ├── sops/                # 14 SOPs\n320: │   ├── standards/           # Operating manual + ADRs\n321: │   └── index.html           # Landing page\n322: ├── ROADMAP.md               # RICE-scored reader priorities\n323: ├── CHANGELOG.md             # Version history\n324: ├── PRD.md                   # Product requirements\n325: └── LICENSE                  # Apache 2.0\n326: ```\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ## Roadmap\n331: \n332: See [ROADMAP.md](ROADMAP.md) for the full RICE-scored roadmap across all 33 tools.\n333: \n334: **Next readers:** Cursor, Cline, Aider, Gemini CLI, Copilot\n335: \n336: **Version targets:**\n337: - v0.2.0 (Aug 2026): 10+ readers, real-world data\n338: - v0.3.0 (Sep 2026): 15+ readers, sample corpus\n339: - v1.0.0 (Oct 2026): 20+ readers, stable API\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## Standards\n344: \n345: - [Operating Manual](https://andiekobbietks.github.io/AgentSON/standards/) — Mental models, coding standards, workflow rules\n346: - [ADRs](https://andiekobbietks.github.io/AgentSON/standards/) — Architecture Decision Records (11 ADRs)\n347: - [SOPs](https://andiekobbietks.github.io/AgentSON/sops/) — 14 Standard Operating Procedures\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ## License\n352: \n353: [Apache 2.0](LICENSE) — Patent grant + attribution required.\n354: \n355: ---\n356: \n357: *\"The format that AI companies spend billions to own, AgentSON gives away for free.\"*\n\n(End of file - total 357 lines)\n</content>",
