      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\wiki\\ADRs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)\n2: \n3: ADRs capture significant architectural decisions with context and rationale.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## ADR Index\n8: \n9: | # | Title | Date | Status |\n10: |---|-------|------|--------|\n11: | 001 | [AgentSON Format](ADR-001) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n12: | 002 | [JSON over SQLite](ADR-002) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n13: | 003 | [Vendor Neutral](ADR-003) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n14: | 004 | [Amber Design Tokens](ADR-004) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n15: | 005 | [Nightscout Integration](ADR-005) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n16: | 006 | [GitHub Pages](ADR-006) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n17: | 007 | [CodeRabbit](ADR-007) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n18: | 008 | [Trace Data Interchange](ADR-008) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n19: | 009 | [OSI Open Interchange](ADR-009) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n20: | 010 | [GDPR Data Liberation](ADR-010) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n21: | 011 | [Rename to AgentSON](ADR-011) | 2026-07-05 | Accepted |\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## ADR-001: AgentSON Format\n26: \n27: **Context:** Every AI coding agent stores session data in proprietary SQLite databases with unique schemas. No standard format exists for exporting or sharing session traces.\n28: \n29: **Decision:** Create `.AgentSON` — a single-file JSON format for capturing AI agent session traces with full metadata, tool calls, and reasoning chains.\n30: \n31: **Consequences:**\n32: - (+) One file = one complete session, portable and shareable\n33: - (+) JSON is human-readable and universally supported\n34: - (-) JSON has no binary encoding (larger than SQLite)\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## ADR-002: JSON over SQLite\n39: \n40: **Context:** Session data is stored in SQLite databases locally. Should AgentSON be a SQLite export or a JSON file?\n41: \n42: **Decision:** Use JSON files, not SQLite dumps. Each `.AgentSON` file is self-contained.\n43: \n44: **Consequences:**\n45: - (+) Single file can be emailed, shared, archived\n46: - (+) No database dependency to read\n47: - (-) No indexing (search requires full scan)\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## ADR-003: Vendor Neutral\n52: \n53: **Context:** AgentSON could depend on specific vendor APIs (OpenAI, Anthropic) for enhanced features.\n54: \n55: **Decision:** Never depend on one company's API or format. Every external service is optional. Core features work offline.\n56: \n57: **Consequences:**\n58: - (+) If any vendor shuts down, AgentSON still works\n59: - (+) Users own their data completely\n60: - (-) Can't use vendor-specific features (e.g., OpenAI embeddings)\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## ADR-004: Amber Design Tokens\n65: \n66: **Context:** The original `.ailog` page used cyan/blue tokens (`#58a6ff`). Rebranding to AgentSON required new visual identity.\n67: \n68: **Decision:** Use amber phosphor tokens: `#ffb000` accent, warm dark background, Space Mono + IBM Plex Sans fonts.\n69: \n70: **Consequences:**\n71: - (+) Distinct visual identity from `.ailog`\n72: - (+) Warm, readable dark theme\n73: - (-) Existing `.ailog` users may prefer old colors\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## ADR-010: GDPR Data Liberation\n78: \n79: **Context:** GDPR Article 20 gives users the right to export data in machine-readable format. Most AI tools don't provide this.\n80: \n81: **Decision:** Position AgentSON as the tool to exercise GDPR data rights for AI session data. Add \"Unsloth analogy\" — democratizing data ownership like Unsloth democratized fine-tuning.\n82: \n83: **Consequences:**\n84: - (+) Strong legal and ethical justification\n85: - (+) EU AI Act compliance built-in\n86: - (-) May face resistance from vendors who profit from data lock-in\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## ADR-011: Rename to AgentSON\n91: \n92: **Context:** The project was originally `.ailog`. The name conflicted with existing projects (`hemashushu/ason`, `@ason-format/ason`).\n93: \n94: **Decision:** Rename to AgentSON (Agent + JSON). Use `.agentson` as file extension.\n95: \n96: **Consequences:**\n97: - (+) Clear, descriptive name\n98: - (+) No namespace collisions\n99: - (+) Trademark/name cleared UK/EU/US/PyPI/npm\n100: - (-) Breaking change from `.ailog` format\n\n(End of file - total 100 lines)\n</content>",
