      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\agentsong\\\\SOPs\\\\SOP-006-Sharing-Data-with-Doctors.md\"}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\SOPs\\SOP-006-Sharing-Data-with-Doctors.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # SOP-006: Sharing Data with Doctors\n2: \n3: **Version:** 1.0  \n4: **Date:** 05 July 2026  \n5: **Author:** Andrea Enning (AndieKobbieTech)\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: This SOP describes how to export and share glucose data and AI session insights with healthcare professionals (GPs, consultants, diabetes nurses).\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Prerequisites\n16: \n17: | Item | Requirement |\n18: |------|-------------|\n19: | **Input** | `.AgentSON` file with glucose data |\n20: | **Software** | AgentSON CLI, web browser |\n21: | **Output** | HTML report or PDF |\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## Procedure\n26: \n27: ### Step 1: Generate HTML Report\n28: \n29: ```powershell\n30: cd ~/agentson\n31: \n32: # Render glucose data as HTML\n33: python -m cli.main render \"~/Downloads/libre_libre_data.AgentSON\" --format html --output \"~/Downloads/glucose_report.html\"\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ### Step 2: Open Report in Browser\n37: \n38: ```powershell\n39: Start-Process \"~/Downloads/glucose_report.html\"\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ### Step 3: Print to PDF (Optional)\n43: \n44: 1. Press `Ctrl+P` in browser\n45: 2. Select \"Microsoft Print to PDF\"\n46: 3. Save as `glucose_report.pdf`\n47: \n48: ### Step 4: Share with Doctor\n49: \n50: **Option A: Email**\n51: 1. Attach PDF to email\n52: 2. Send to practice email (check with reception)\n53: \n54: **Option B: Patient Access**\n55: 1. Upload to NHS App (if available)\n56: 2. Share during appointment\n57: \n58: **Option C: In-Person**\n59: 1. Bring printed report to appointment\n60: 2. Bring phone/laptop with web viewer loaded\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## What to Share\n65: \n66: | Data | Why |\n67: |------|-----|\n68: | **Time in Range** | Shows how often glucose is in target zone |\n69: | **Average Glucose** | Overall control indicator |\n70: | **Hypo/Hyper %** | Safety concerns |\n71: | **Trends** | Patterns over time |\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## NHS FHIR Integration (Future)\n76: \n77: When available, this will allow:\n78: - Automatic sharing with clinical systems\n79: - Real-time data access for doctors\n80: - Integration with NHS App\n81: \n82: See SOP-007 for Nightscout setup which enables FHIR connectivity.\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## Tips for Appointments\n87: \n88: 1. **Bring printed report** — doctors appreciate paper\n89: 2. **Highlight concerns** — mark specific dates/times\n90: 3. **Ask questions** — \"Is this pattern concerning?\"\n91: 4. **Request sensor replacement** — if running low\n\n(End of file - total 91 lines)\n</content>",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1783296352020
