      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\SOPs\\SOP-001-Reading-FreeStyle-Libre-2-Sensor.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # SOP-001: Reading FreeStyle Libre 2 Sensor\n2: \n3: **Version:** 1.0  \n4: **Date:** 05 July 2026  \n5: **Author:** Andrea Enning (AndieKobbieTech)\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: This SOP describes how to connect a FreeStyle Libre 2 reader to a Windows PC via USB and extract glucose data for analysis and storage.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Prerequisites\n16: \n17: | Item | Requirement |\n18: |------|-------------|\n19: | **Hardware** | FreeStyle Libre 2 reader with USB cable |\n20: | **Software** | Python 3.12.3, glucometerutils, freestyle-hid |\n21: | **Data** | Sensor must have readings stored on the reader |\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## Setup (One-Time)\n26: \n27: ### Step 1: Create Python Virtual Environment\n28: \n29: ```powershell\n30: cd ~/Documents\n\n(Showing lines 1-30 of 108. Use offset=31 to continue.)\n</content>",
