      "text": "Here is my comprehensive report on the AgentSON repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Full Directory Structure\n\nThe main repository lives at **`C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong`** (lowercase), with a companion wiki at **`C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\AgentSON.wiki`** (the GitHub wiki clone).\n\n### Main Repository (`agentsong/`)\n\n| Path | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `README.md` | Project overview and quick start |\n| `pyproject.toml` | Python package metadata |\n| `PRD.md` | Product Requirements Document |\n| `ROADMAP.md` | RICE-scoped reader priorities |\n| `CHANGELOG.md` | Version history |\n| `PERSONAS-AND-USER-STORIES.md` | Personas & user stories |\n| `setup.py` / `MANIFEST.in` | Python packaging |\n| `LICENSE` | Apache 2.0 |\n| `index.html` | Project landing page |\n| `install.ps1` | Windows install script |\n| `agentson_cli.py` | CLI entry point |\n| `check_opencode.py` | Utility script |\n| `wiki_cheatsheet.py` | Wiki generation utility |\n| | |\n| **`spec/`** | JSON Schema definitions |\n| `spec/v1.json` | Schema v1 |\n| `spec/v1.1.json` | Schema v1.1 (trajectory semantics) |\n| | |\n| **`readers/`** | Tool-specific readers |\n| `readers/__init__.py` | Reader exports |\n| `readers/opencode.py` | opencode reader (Working) |\n| `readers/minimax.py` | MiniMax reader (Working) |\n| `readers/antigravity.py` | Antigravity IDE reader (Working) |\n| `readers/libre.py` | FreeStyle Libre 2 reader (Working) |\n| `readers/chrome_devtools.py` | Chrome DevTools AI reader (Working) |\n| `readers/claude_code.py` | Claude Code reader (Working) |\n| `readers/cursor.py` | Cursor reader (Working) |\n| `readers/cline.py` | Cline reader (Working) |\n| `readers/aider.py` | Aider reader (Working) |\n| | |\n| **`cli/`** | Command-line interface |\n| `cli/main.py` | CLI entry point |\n| `cli/supabase_client.py` | Supabase integration |\n| | |\n| **`exporters/`** | Format exporters |\n| `exporters/finetune.py` | Unsloth + Olive fine-tuning export |\n| | |\n| **`importers/`** | Data importers |\n| `importers/chatgpt.py` | ChatGPT conversations.json importer |\n| | |\n| **`normalizer/`** | Data normalizer (tool-specific to AgentSON) |\n| | |\n| **`renderers/`** | Output renderers |\n| | |\n| **`viewers/`** | Web viewers |\n| `viewers/web/index.html` | Drag-and-drop web viewer |\n| | |\n| **`docs/`** | Live documentation site (GitHub Pages) |\n| `docs/index.html` | Landing page |\n| `docs/404.html` | Custom 404 |\n| `docs/.nojekyll` | GitHub Pages config |\n| `docs/standards/` | Standards docs |\n| `docs/standards/index.html` | Standards index |\n| `docs/standards/render.html` | Standards renderer |\n| `docs/standards/README.md` | Standards README |\n| `docs/standards/workflow.md` | Workflow rules |\n| `docs/standards/coding-standards.md` | Coding standards |\n| `docs/standards/mental-models.md` | Mental models |\n| `docs/standards/adrs/` | **ADRs (12 files)** |\n| `docs/sops/` | **SOPs (mirrored from SOPs/)** |\n| `docs/sops/index.html` | SOPs index |\n| `docs/sops/render.html` | SOPs renderer |\n| `docs/spec/trajectory-view.md` | Trajectory view spec |\n| `docs/viewer/index.html` | Web viewer |\n| `docs/dev/index.html` | Dev docs |\n| | |\n| **`SOPs/`** | Standard Operating Procedures (14 files) |\n| `SOPs/SOP-001-*` through `SOP-014-*` | See SOP section below |\n| | |\n| **`issues/`** | Design issues / discussions |\n| `issues/issue-healthcare-data-interoperability.md` | Healthcare data interoperability |\n| `issues/issue-competitive-landscape-agentlog.md` | Competitive landscape |\n| `issues/issue-design-principle-intrinsic-before-extrinsic.md` | Design principle |\n| `issues/issue-new-readers.md` | New readers |\n| | |\n| **`tests/`** | Test suite |\n| `tests/test_opencode.py` | opencode tests |\n| `tests/test_minimax.py` | MiniMax tests |\n| `tests/test_antigravity.py` | Antigravity tests |\n| `tests/test_claude_code.py` | Claude Code tests |\n| `tests/test_chrome_devtools.py` | Chrome DevTools tests |\n| `tests/test_cursor.py` | Cursor tests |\n| `tests/test_cline.py` | Cline tests |\n| `tests/test_aider.py` | Aider tests |\n| | |\n| **`examples/`** | Example `.AgentSON` files |\n| `examples/opencode_example.AgentSON` | opencode example |\n| `examples/minimax_example.AgentSON` | MiniMax example |\n| `examples/antigravity_example.AgentSON` | Antigravity example |\n| `examples/devtools_download_this_video_in_the_scene.AgentSON` | DevTools example |\n| `examples/cursor-cline-aider-readers-session.AgentSON` | Cursor/Cline/Aider example |\n| | |\n| **`pwa/`** | Progressive Web App |\n| `pwa/index.html`, `pwa/sw.js`, `pwa/manifest.json` | PWA viewer |\n| | |\n| **`wiki/`** | Local wiki content |\n| `wiki/Home.md`, `wiki/ADRs.md`, etc. | Wiki markdown |\n| `wiki/AgentSON_Wiki_Cheatsheet.pdf` | Wiki cheatsheet PDF |\n| | |\n| **`supabase/`** | Cloud backend |\n| `supabase/schema.sql` | Supabase schema |\n| | |\n| **`training/`** | ML training data |\n| `training/opencode_example_unsloth.jsonl` | Example for Unsloth |\n| | |\n| `agentson.egg-info/` | Python egg info |\n| `.pytest_cache/` | Pytest cache |\n| `.gitignore` | Git ignore |\n\n### Wiki (`AgentSON.wiki/`)\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `Home.md` | Wiki home page |\n| `Getting-Started.md` | Quick start guide |\n| `Schema.md` | JSON Schema reference |\n| `Readers.md` | Reader status & plans |\n| `ADRs.md` | Architecture Decision Records index |\n| `SOPs.md` | Standard Operating Procedures index |\n| `SOP-015-Creating-GitHub-Wiki.md` | SOP for wiki creation |\n| `Coding-Standards.md` | Coding standards |\n| `Mental-Models.md` | Design mental models |\n| `Contributing.md` | How to contribute |\n\n---\n\n## 2. ADRs (Architecture Decision Records)\n\nAll ADRs are located in `docs/standards/adrs/`. There are **12 ADRs** total:\n\n| # | Title | Status | File |\n|---|-------|--------|------|\n| 001 | **Why AgentSON Exists as a Format** | Accepted | `adr-001-agentSON-format.md` |\n| 002 | **Why JSON Files Over SQLite Databases** | Accepted | `adr-002-json-over-sqlite.md` |\n| 003 | **Why Vendor Neutrality Matters** | Accepted | `adr-003-vendor-neutral.md` |\n| 004 | **Why Amber Phosphor Design Tokens** | Accepted | `adr-004-amber-design.md` |\n| 005 | **Why Nightscout Over Proprietary CGM Systems** | Accepted | `adr-005-nightscout.md` |\n| 006 | **Why GitHub Pages Over Vercel/Netlify** | Accepted | `adr-006-github-pages.md` |\n| 007 | **Why CodeRabbit for Reviews (and Why Not Required)** | Accepted | `adr-007-coderabbit.md` |\n| 008 | **AgentSON as the Open Interchange Layer for AI Workflow Traces** | Accepted | `adr-008-trace-data-interchange.md` |\n| 009 | **AgentSON as Open Interchange Format for OSI Open Source AI** | Accepted | `adr-009-osi-open-interchange.md` |\n| 010 | **AgentSON as GDPR/EU AI Act Data Liberation Tool** | Accepted | `adr-010-gdpr-data-liberation.md` |\n| 011 | **Rename from agenson to AgentSON** | Accepted | `adr-011-rename-agenson-to-agentsone.md` |\n| 012 | **Intrinsic Before Extrinsic** | **Proposed** | `adr-012-intrinsic-before-extrinsic.md` |\n\nAll ADRs are authored by **Andrea Enning** (AndieKobbieTech). ADRs 001-011 are **Accepted** (dated 04-05 July 2026). ADR-012 is **Proposed**.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Issues (`issues/` directory)\n\nFour issue files exist:\n\n| Issue | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `issue-healthcare-data-interoperability.md` | GDPR/healthcare data rights analysis |\n| `issue-competitive-landscape-agentlog.md` | Competitive comparison with AgentLog |\n| `issue-design-principle-intrinsic-before-extrinsic.md` | Proposal for design principle |\n| `issue-new-readers.md` | Adding Cursor, Cline, Aider readers |\n\n---\n\n## 4. GDPR and Healthcare-Related Documents\n\n### Primary: `issues/issue-healthcare-data-interoperability.md`\n\n**Full contents** (already returned above -- 114 lines). This document covers:\n\n- **Legal context** -- GDPR Article 20 (right to data portability), ICO guidance, what GDPR requires vs. doesn't require\n- **Healthcare interoperability angle** -- FDA position, clinical decision latency, NHS FHIR mandate, CMS Interop Rule (US), information blocking provisions, real-world litigation (Epic vs. Health Gorilla), clinical outcomes from interoperability\n- **Why Abbott doesn't have APIs** -- regulatory liability, clinical interpretation control, cybersecurity, commercial lock-in\n- **AgentSON's role** -- an interoperability representation layer, not a law enforcement tool\n- **Sources** -- 8 cited references with URLs\n\n### Key compliance-related documents:\n\n| File | Relevance |\n|------|-----------|\n| **ADR-010: GDPR Data Liberation** (`docs/standards/adrs/adr-010-gdpr-data-liberation.md`) | Full 103-line ADR positioning AgentSON as GDPR/EU AI Act data liberation tool -- the \"Unsloth of session data\" |\n| **ADR-012: Intrinsic Before Extrinsic** | Defines compliance as an **extrinsic** concern outside the core spec |\n| **SOP-013: NHS FHIR Integration** | Healthcare interoperability with NHS clinical systems |\n| **SOP-006: Sharing Data with Doctors** | How to share glucose data with healthcare professionals |\n| **SOP-011: Fine-tuning MedGemma on Glucose Data** | Mentions HIPAA compliance (keep data local, don't upload to cloud) |\n| **README.md** | References GDPR Art. 20, EU AI Act Art. 52 as core value props |\n| **Wiki Home.md** | Same GDPR/EU AI Act references |\n\n### Compliance mentions found across 38 matches in the repository including:\n- **GDPR Article 20** (Right to data portability) -- referenced in README, ADR-010, Home.md, issue-healthcare\n- **EU AI Act Article 52** (Transparency) -- referenced in README, ADR-010\n- **HIPAA** -- mentioned once in SOP-011 (fine-tuning context)\n- **NHS FHIR** -- covered in SOP-013 and issue-healthcare\n- **CMS Interop Rule / ONC Cures Act** (US) -- referenced in issue-healthcare\n- **Information blocking** (US) -- referenced in issue-healthcare\n\n---\n\n## 5. README.md Summary\n\nThe project is **AgentSON** (\"Agent + JSON\") -- an open interchange format for AI agent session traces, licensed under **Apache 2.0**. Key points:\n\n- Started with a FreeStyle Libre 2 glucose monitor (health data lock-in problem)\n- Expanded to cover all AI coding agent sessions\n- **GDPR Article 20** and **EU AI Act** are core legal justifications\n- Currently has **9 working readers** (opencode, minimax, antigravity, libre, chrome_devtools, claude_code, cursor, cline, aider)\n- **33 tools** planned across 7 tiers\n- CLI tool for export, search, render, fine-tune\n- Fine-tuning export to Unsloth/Olive formats\n- PWA viewer for drag-and-drop session viewing\n- \"The Unsloth of session data\" -- democratizing data ownership\n\n---\n\n## 6. pyproject.toml Summary\n\n- **Package name:** `agentson`\n- **Version:** `0.1.0`\n- **Description:** \"Agent + JSON -- vendor-neutral session capture format for AI coding agents\"\n- **License:** Apache-2.0\n- **Python:** >=3.9\n- **Author:** andiekobbietks\n- **Dependencies:** `requests>=2.28`\n- **Optional:** `pytest>=7.0`, `pyrefly>=0.1`\n- **Entry point:** `agentson = cli.main:main`\n- **CLI registered as console script**\n\n---\n\n## 7. SOPs / Compliance Guides\n\nThere are **14 SOPs** in `SOPs/` (mirrored in `docs/sops/`) plus **1 wiki-specific SOP**:\n\n| # | Name | Category |\n|---|------|----------|\n| 001 | Reading FreeStyle Libre 2 Sensor | Health |\n| 002 | Converting Libre Data to AgentSON | Health |\n| 003 | Viewing Glucose Data in Browser | Health |\n| 004 | Exporting AI Sessions | AI Sessions |\n| 005 | Searching AI Sessions | AI Sessions |\n| 006 | **Sharing Data with Doctors** | Health |\n| 007 | Setting Up Nightscout Server | Infrastructure |\n| 008 | WhatsApp Bot Setup | Infrastructure |\n| 009 | TV Dashboard Setup | Infrastructure |\n| 010 | Setting Up MedGemma HAI-DEF | Health/AI |\n| 011 | **Fine-tuning MedGemma on Glucose Data** (mentions HIPAA) | Health/AI |\n| 012 | Setting Up Juggluco on Mother's Phone | Health |\n| 013 | **NHS FHIR Integration** | Health |\n| 014 | West Africa Voice Alerts | Health/Localization |\n| 015 | Creating GitHub Wiki (in AgentSON.wiki) | Infrastructure |\n\n**Compliance-related SOPs** specifically are:\n- **SOP-006** -- Sharing data with doctors (patient data handling)\n- **SOP-011** -- Mentions HIPAA compliance (keep data local)\n- **SOP-013** -- NHS FHIR integration (healthcare system interoperability)\n\nThere is **no dedicated compliance/SOP guide** beyond what is embedded in these procedures. Compliance concerns are primarily addressed in:\n- ADR-010 (GDPR/EU AI Act as legal foundation)\n- issue-healthcare-data-interoperability.md (detailed legal analysis)\n- The four intrinsic properties in ADR-012 (compliance is extrinsic)\n\n---\n\n## Final Summary of All ADRs with Their Titles\n\n| ADR | Full Title | Status |\n|-----|-----------|--------|\n| **001** | Why AgentSON Exists as a Format | Accepted |\n| **002** | Why JSON Files Over SQLite Databases | Accepted |\n| **003** | Why Vendor Neutrality Matters | Accepted |\n| **004** | Why Amber Phosphor Design Tokens | Accepted |\n| **005** | Why Nightscout Over Proprietary CGM Systems | Accepted |\n| **006** | Why GitHub Pages Over Vercel/Netlify | Accepted |\n| **007** | Why CodeRabbit for Reviews (and Why Not Required) | Accepted |\n| **008** | AgentSON as the Open Interchange Layer for AI Workflow Traces | Accepted |\n| **009** | AgentSON as Open Interchange Format for OSI Open Source AI | Accepted |\n| **010** | AgentSON as GDPR/EU AI Act Data Liberation Tool | Accepted |\n| **011** | Rename from agenson to AgentSON | Accepted |\n| **012** | Intrinsic Before Extrinsic | **Proposed** |\n\nAll ADR files (with full contents) can be found at:\n`C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\docs\\standards\\adrs\\adr-*.md`",
